## Challenge

I’d always wanted to build a machine that draws. When my budget 3D printer broke, I saw it as an opportunity: instead of fixing it, I decided to take it apart and use the parts to build a pen plotter — a robot that moves a pen across paper to create illustrations.

My first version worked, but had some issues: the drawing surface was too small, and the arm that held the pen wobbled at the edges. So I started over — this time designing a sturdier frame, rethinking how the pen would lift and drop, and learning just enough 3D modeling to design custom parts.

