## Approach

The plotter is made from aluminum rails, recycled motors, and 3D-printed brackets — most of which I designed myself. I learned how to model in Fusion 360 by trial and error, referencing online examples and tutorials.

The machine is controlled by a tiny circuit board and a modified open-source firmware. I also use a small computer (a Raspberry Pi) to connect to it remotely and send it drawing instructions.

To create the artwork, I write code using **p5.js**, a tool for generative drawing. Then I refine the images in Inkscape and convert them into a format the machine understands. I’ve also started building my own set of tools to speed up and automate this part of the process.

